<subSubSection pageId="16" pageNumber="133" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,297,1286,1311]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">Description.</emphasis>
Body (
<figureCitation box="[381,492,1287,1311]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. a – d" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1574,1597]" captionTargetBox="[185,1407,567,1535]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[172,1415,555,1552]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. a – d. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; e – h. Kapsa (Rigida? imminuta Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; i – l. Kapsa (Rigida? megaprocessa Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; m – p. Kapsa (Rigida) serrata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222872/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[435,450,1287,1311]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="2.0">2</number>
a, b
</figureCitation>
) brown, forewing light brownish, brochosome filed yellow, clavus brown. Coronal suture (
<figureCitation box="[235,315,1322,1346]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. a – d" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1574,1597]" captionTargetBox="[185,1407,567,1535]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[172,1415,555,1552]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. a – d. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; e – h. Kapsa (Rigida? imminuta Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; i – l. Kapsa (Rigida? megaprocessa Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; m – p. Kapsa (Rigida) serrata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222872/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[287,302,1322,1346]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="2.0">2</number>
c
</figureCitation>
) distinct, exceeding midlength of vertex. Face (
<figureCitation box="[849,931,1322,1346]" captionStart="FIGURE 2. a – d" captionStartId="8.[151,250,1574,1597]" captionTargetBox="[185,1407,567,1535]" captionTargetId="figure@8.[172,1415,555,1552]" captionTargetPageId="8" captionText="FIGURE 2. a – d. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; e – h. Kapsa (Rigida? imminuta Yang &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; i – l. Kapsa (Rigida? megaprocessa Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov.; m – p. Kapsa (Rigida) serrata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222872/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[902,916,1322,1346]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="2.0">2</number>
d
</figureCitation>
) flattened in lateral view, relatively short.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Abdominal apodemes (
<figureCitation box="[460,541,1361,1385]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,189,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1410,171,1150]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. forewing; b. hind wing; c. abdominal apodemes; d. genital capsule; e. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; f. subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view; g. subgenital plate, dorsal view; h. paramere, lateral view; i. connective; j. aedeagus, lateral view; k. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222880/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[512,541,1361,1385]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
c) small, not extending to hind margin of 
<number box="[1007,1021,1361,1385]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="3.0">3</number>
rd sternite. Anal tube appendage (
<figureCitation captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,189,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1410,171,1150]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. forewing; b. hind wing; c. abdominal apodemes; d. genital capsule; e. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; f. subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view; g. subgenital plate, dorsal view; h. paramere, lateral view; i. connective; j. aedeagus, lateral view; k. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222880/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[151,180,1397,1421]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
d, e) slim and long.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1286,1889]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Pygofer dorsal appendage (
<figureCitation box="[508,590,1433,1457]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,189,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1410,171,1150]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. forewing; b. hind wing; c. abdominal apodemes; d. genital capsule; e. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; f. subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view; g. subgenital plate, dorsal view; h. paramere, lateral view; i. connective; j. aedeagus, lateral view; k. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222880/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[561,590,1433,1457]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
d, e) short, tapering apically, curved ventrad. Subgenital plate (
<figureCitation box="[1302,1385,1433,1457]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,189,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1410,171,1150]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. forewing; b. hind wing; c. abdominal apodemes; d. genital capsule; e. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; f. subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view; g. subgenital plate, dorsal view; h. paramere, lateral view; i. connective; j. aedeagus, lateral view; k. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222880/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[1356,1385,1433,1457]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
d, g) with 
<number box="[210,224,1469,1493]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="6.0">6</number>
macrosetae laterally, basal stout microsetae and apical rigid microsetae forming continuous row laterally. Paramere (
<figureCitation box="[277,362,1505,1529]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,189,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1410,171,1150]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. forewing; b. hind wing; c. abdominal apodemes; d. genital capsule; e. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; f. subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view; g. subgenital plate, dorsal view; h. paramere, lateral view; i. connective; j. aedeagus, lateral view; k. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222880/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[334,362,1505,1529]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
h) resembling that of 
<taxonomicName box="[623,800,1506,1530]" class="Insecta" family="Cicadellidae" genus="Kapsa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="aculeiformis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis box="[623,800,1506,1530]" italics="true" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">K. aculeiformis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[812,907,1506,1530]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" rank="species">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[812,907,1506,1530]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">sp. nov.</emphasis>
</taxonomicNameLabel>
, but apical branch as long as the basal one, preapical lobe small. Connective (
<figureCitation box="[540,623,1541,1565]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,189,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1410,171,1150]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. forewing; b. hind wing; c. abdominal apodemes; d. genital capsule; e. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; f. subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view; g. subgenital plate, dorsal view; h. paramere, lateral view; i. connective; j. aedeagus, lateral view; k. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222880/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[594,623,1541,1565]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">
<date box="[594,623,1541,1565]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="2010-01">10</date>
</number>
</figureCitation>
i) with lateral arms long, manubrium short. Aedeagal shaft (
<figureCitation box="[1307,1390,1541,1565]" captionStart="FIGURE 10" captionStartId="17.[151,250,1159,1182]" captionTargetBox="[192,1392,189,1136]" captionTargetId="figure@17.[176,1410,171,1150]" captionTargetPageId="17" captionText="FIGURE 10. Kapsa (Rigida) furcata Cao &amp; Zhang sp. nov. a. forewing; b. hind wing; c. abdominal apodemes; d. genital capsule; e. pygofer dorsal appendage and anal tube appendage, lateral view; f. subgenital plate, paramere and connective, dorsal view; g. subgenital plate, dorsal view; h. paramere, lateral view; i. connective; j. aedeagus, lateral view; k. aedeagus, ventral view." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/222880/files/figure.png" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
Fig. 
<number box="[1361,1390,1541,1565]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" value="10.0">10</number>
</figureCitation>
j, k) compressed laterally, ventral process slender and short, approximately half length of aedeagal shaft; gonopore terminal, ventral.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="16.[151,1436,1286,1889]" box="[199,677,1649,1674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,371,1650,1674]" pageId="16" pageNumber="133">Measurement.</emphasis>
Body length: male 
<quantity box="[591,673,1649,1673]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.3" pageId="16" pageNumber="133" unit="mm" value="3.3">3.3mm</quantity>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
